WORLD BASEBALL CLASSIC POOL C: TORONTO
March 10, 2009
Jack Santora
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT









   JACK SANTORA: Get anything started early, get a few hits and a few runs in, and next thing you know, it turned on us. Once their bats woke up, that was it.

 Q. Those two times you loaded bases, but there was --
 JACK SANTORA: A big hit. That's what you look for in every game. We had it last night, but today, it just didn't happen.

 Q. But it's just because you were really -- you know, after winning last night something turned off?
 JACK SANTORA: I don't think that was it. I think last night was the first night we actually came together, and it felt like this whole trip started, like we've really gelled. And I felt like it was going to really take off today, and we were going to upset them. Unfortunately, it didn't happen.







END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT